name: Warren Buffett
scoringHints: Wonderful company at a fair price. Moat and quality dominate; macro and sentiment ignored. Willing to pay up for durable competitive advantages and disciplined capital allocators.

name: Benjamin Graham
scoringHints: Deep value with a large margin of safety. Statistical cheapness and balance sheet safety dominate. Skeptical of growth forecasts; ignores narrative and sentiment entirely.

name: Peter Lynch
scoringHints: Growth at a reasonable price (GARP). PEG ratio is the primary valuation check. Earnings acceleration and sector narrative matter; invest in what you understand.
